Attending 14 million tourists annually Broughton Street Caters
to both the traveler and the local consumer. Historic downtown
is a mix of best in class national, regional and local retailers
along with a residential component for the creative class
and professionals. Many tenants choose Broughton Street
as their only location including Lululemon, Vineyard Vines,
Anthropology, Kate Spade, Banana Republic, Midge, Steve
Madden, and Dress Up.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
• Woodstock Square is located just around the corner from the downtown Woodstock district, which has become a
prototype for thoughtful redevelopment of suburban main streets in Atlanta. The district features live music venues,
chef-driven restaurants and green space and has become a catalyst for surrounding residential growth.

• Woodstock Square is flanked by a handful of significant residential projects drafting off of the suburban
renaissance in Woodstock. Pulte is under construction on a project that shares a border with Woodstock
Square featuring 80 townhomes. Adjacent to that project is The View at Woodstock, an apartment development which
recently brought 320 multihousing units online.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Woodstock Square is located in close proximity to the Outlet
Shoppes of Atlanta and Woodstock, GA’s historic downtown
area. The center is well-positioned on Georgia State Route 92
and offers convenient access from I-575.
